The paper proposes a deep learning model for 3D surface prediction, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The model is end-to-end trainable and incorporates a variational shape inference formulation, which suggests the use of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) methods. The paper also introduces a novel geometric loss function, which may involve numerical optimization (NE) techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE, in that order.
